x4codes.hlp: INFN Laboratori Nazionali di Frascati, Frascati, Italy

x4freetext: LEALE FACILITY.
LEALE QUASIMONOChROMATIC PHOTON BEAM
PRODUCED BY POSITRON IN FLIGFHT ANNIHILATION.
MAGNETIC SPECTROMETER.
THE DEUTERIUM TARGET CONSISTED OF A VERTICAL MYLAR
CYLINDER (40 MM DIAMETER, 0.08 MM WALL THICKNESS)
FILLED WITH LIQUID DEUTERIUM.
A MONTE CARLO PROGRAM (TARGET) HAS BEEN USED TO
ACCOUNT FOR THE EFFECTS TO FINITE PHOTON BEAM AND
EXTENDED TARGET GEOMETRY ON THE PROTON DETECTORS.
THE PROGRAM SIMULATED THE EXPERIMENTAL PHOTOPROTON
SPECTRA INCLUDING, FOR EACH EVENT, ALL THE
CORRECTIONS SUCH AS ACTUAL SOLID ANGLE, MULTIPLE
SCATTERING AND ENERGY LOSSES IN THE TARGET AND
SCINTILLATORS, RESCATTERING BY THE COLLIMATORS,
NUCLEAR ABSORPTION, AND EDGE EFFECTS IN THE NAI
DETECTORS. INPUT DATA WERE THE MEASURED PHOTON
SPECTRUM, THE COMPLETE GEOMETRY OF THE APPARATUS,
AND A TRIAL PHOTODISINTEGRATION CROSS SECTION
WHICH WAS ITERATED UNTIL THE SIMULATED SPECTRUM
BECAME COMPATIBLE, WITHIN STATISTICAL ERRORS,
WITH THE MEASURED PROTON ENERGY DISTRIBUTION.

x4code.headerHelp: Error in value of quantity, defined under ERR-ANALYS

x4freetext: STATISTICAL ERRORS. SYSTEMATIC
UNCERTAINTIES WERE ESTIMATED TO BE 5 %.
DIFFERENTIAL CROSS SECTIONS FOR THE 2H(G,P)N
REACTION WERE MEASURED AT FIVE LABORATORY ANGLES
FROM 32.5 TO 130 DEGREE, FOR PHOTON ENERGIES
BETWEEN 100 AND 255 MEV, IN 10 MEV STEPS. A
QUASIMONOCHROMATIC PHOTON BEAM. OBTAINED BY
POSITRON IN-FLIGHT ANNIHILATION ON LIQUID HYDROGEN
RADIATOR, WAS USED, AND THE PHOTON SPECTRUM
MEASURED ON-LINE BY A PAIR SPECTROMETER. THE
NORMALIZATION UNCERTAINTY IS WITHIN 5 %. DATA AGREE,
WITHIN THE TOTAL ERRORS, WITH RECENT RESULTS OF A
TAGGED-PHOTON EXPERIMENT AMD OF A MEASUREMENT OF THE
INVERSE PROCESS. THE MEASURED ANGULAR DISTRIBUTIONS
WERE FITTED BY A SUM OF LEGENDRE POLYNOMIAS, AND THE
RESULTS COMPARED WITH RECENT CALCULATIONS.
SIGNIFICANT DEPARTURES FROM THE CALCULATED ANGULAR
DISTRIBUTION ASYMMETRY HAVE BEEN FOUND.
DATA FROM THE TABLE 1.
DATA WERE COMPILED AT THE USA BNL NNDC BY
V.V.VARLAMOV.
